---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Leadership Principles" description="Core principles for leading ruck crews effectively">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Leadership Principles</h1>
  <div class="prose lg:prose-xl mx-auto">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
      <p>Effective leadership is the foundation of a successful ruck club. These principles guide leaders in creating positive, impactful experiences for all members while fostering growth and camaraderie.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Core Principles</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Lead by Example: Demonstrate the commitment, attitude, and effort you expect from others.</li>
        <li>Serve First: Prioritize the needs and development of your members above personal recognition.</li>
        <li>Communicate Clearly: Share information openly, listen actively, and provide constructive feedback.</li>
        <li>Develop Others: Invest time in mentoring and creating opportunities for members to grow.</li>
        <li>Foster Inclusivity: Create an environment where everyone feels welcome and valued regardless of background or ability.</li>
        <li>Embrace Adaptability: Adjust plans and approaches based on circumstances while maintaining core objectives.</li>
        <li>Ensure Safety: Prioritize proper form, injury prevention, and risk management in all activities.</li>
        <li>Build Community: Create connections and shared experiences that strengthen bonds between members.</li>
        <li>Maintain Consistency: Provide reliable leadership and steady progress toward established goals.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Practical Checklist</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li>Conduct regular one-on-one check-ins with club members.</li>
        <li>Seek feedback after each ruck to improve future events.</li>
        <li>Rotate leadership responsibilities to develop emerging leaders.</li>
        <li>Organize social events outside of rucks to build stronger relationships.</li>
        <li>Recognize and celebrate member achievements and milestones.</li>
        <li>Stay informed on best practices for safety and effective group leadership.</li>
        <li>Plan progressive challenges that match the group's developing capabilities.</li>
        <li>Document lessons learned and share them with the leadership team.</li>
        <li>Regularly revisit and reinforce the club's mission and values.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">Downloadable Checklist</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/checklists/leadership-principles.pdf" class="btn btn-primary" download>
          Download Printable Checklist (PDF)
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
